fr.inrialpes.exmo.align.impl

Class BitSetDisjunctiveRelation<T extends BaseRelation>

  • java.lang.Object
    • fr.inrialpes.exmo.align.impl.BasicRelation
      • fr.inrialpes.exmo.align.impl.BitSetDisjunctiveRelation<T>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    DisjunctiveRelation<T>, java.lang.Iterable<T>, Relation, Visitable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    BitSetAlgebraRelation

    public abstract class BitSetDisjunctiveRelation<T extends BaseRelation>
extends BasicRelation
implements DisjunctiveRelation<T>, java.lang.Iterable<T>
    Represents a dijunctive ontology alignment relation implementation. A disjunctive ontology alignment relation is made of the disjunction of several atomic relations. This disjunction is traditionally represented as a set, here implemented as BitSets
    Version:
    $Id: BitSetDisjunctiveRelation.java 2129 2017-03-04 17:51:55Z euzenat $
